    {
     "type": "html",
     "name": "question2",
     "width": "600px",
     "minWidth": "600px",
     "maxWidth": "600px",
     "html": "<p></p><h4 style=\"text-align:Right\">\nUCSD Project 802055</h4><p></p>\n\n<p></p><h4 style=\"text-align:Right\">\nAdult Consent</h4><p></p>\n\n\n\n<p><br /></p><h3 style=\"text-align:center\"> <b>University of California, San Diego</b></h3><p></p>\n\n<p></p><h3 style=\"text-align:center\"> <b>Consent to Act as a Research Subject and Parent Consent for a Child to Act as a Research Subject</b></h3> <p></p>\n\n<p></p><h4 style=\"text-align:center\"><b>\nThe HEALthy Brain and Child Development (HBCD) Pilot Study</b></h4><p></p>\n\n<p><br /></p><h4 style=\"text-align:left\"><b><i>Introduction</i></b></h4><p></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:left;color:black;font-size:16px\">Dr. Gretchen Bandoli and Dr. Sheila Gahagan are conducting a pilot study for research at UC San Diego, and are asking for your consent for you and your child to participate. The purpose is to help find out if the planned study activities are acceptable and can be completed by future participants. This pilot study will recruit between 10 and 31 pilot participants at each of 25 locations across the United States where the main study will also be done. This section provides a summary of important information. The rest of the form provides additional details. </p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:left;color:black;font-size:16px\">The purpose of this pilot study is to inform a nation-wide research project that is intended to learn how children grow and change (develop) early in life. We will study children’s thinking, behavior, social interactions, emotions, and brains from birth through 10 years old. The research will look at many factors that might be helpful or harmful to a child’s development. These include exposure to tobacco, alcohol, and other drugs before birth, family members’ mental health and stress, the family’s social and economic environment, the child’s exposure to toxins, and how the parent or caregiver interacts with their child. The overall goal of this study is to better understand how children grow up in different environments. While there is no direct benefit to you from participating, the results of this study may help scientists design new methods for improving the lives of children and their families. </p>"
    },
    {
     "type": "text",
     "name": "globalID",
     "visible": false,
     "width": "550px",
     "minWidth": "550px",
     "maxWidth": "550px",
     "title": "globalID",
     "surveyVariable": "ParticipantVariable:globalId"
    }
   ],
   "visibleIf": "{fromInternal} = 'Yes'"
  },
  {
   "name": "page3.1",
   "elements": [
    {
     "type": "html",
     "name": "question49",
     "width": "600px",
     "minWidth": "600px",
     "maxWidth": "600px",
     "html": "<p style=\"text-align:left;color:black;font-size:16px\">If you agree for you and or your child to participate, we will ask you to take part in completing one to two visits, either during your pregnancy, at less than 1 month of age for your child, or between 3-9 months of age for your child. These visits will take place in-person, or some parts may be done remotely. The length of visits will vary, and may last between approximately one to seven hours per visit (which can be broken up into multiple visits). This will include completing interviews, questionnaires and other tests about yourself and or your child for the visits that are planned for the first year of the study. We may ask you and or your child to wear small devices for a few days to measure heart rate and or movement. We may ask you and or your child to provide some biological samples. Because this study is looking at how a child’s brain develops in the first years of life, we may ask that you allow your child to have brain scans and other measures of how your child’s brain is developing.  </p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:left;color:black;font-size:16px\"> The most serious potential risks of the study are the social and legal risks that could result the loss of your or your child’s confidentiality if we mistakenly share your information with someone outside the study. Every effort will be made to protect your confidentiality. All records collected from you and your child will be identified by unique study ID and will not carry personal identifiers.</p>\n\n<p><br /></p><h4 style=\"text-align:Leftt\">\nVersion 06/06/2022</h4><p></p>"
    }
   ],
   "visibleIf": "{fromInternal} = 'Yes'"
  },
  {
   "name": "page4",
   "elements": [
    {
     "type": "html",
     "name": "question3",
     "width": "600px",
     "minWidth": "600px",
     "maxWidth": "600px",
     "html": "<ul style=\"font-size:16px;color:black\">\n<li>Research is voluntary - whether or not you agree for you and or your child to participate in this research is your decision. You can discuss your decision with others (such as family, friends, or your or your child’s doctor).</li>\n\n<li>You can say yes but change your mind later.</li>\n\n<li>If you say no, we will not hold your decision against you or your child, and your decision will not affect your or your child’s health care or any other benefits you or your child may be entitled to.</li>\n\n<li>Please ask questions or mention concerns before, during or after the research</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n<p style=\"text-align:left;color:black;font-size:16px\"> Additional, detailed information about this research is provided below. </p>\n\n\n\n<br /><h4 style=\"text-align:left\"><b><i>\nWhy you and your child have been asked to participate, how you and your child were selected, and what is the approximate number of participants in the study? </i></b></h4>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:left;color:black;font-size:16px\">You and or your child have been asked to participate in this pilot study because you live in San Diego County, you are pregnant or you have a child 9 months of age or younger. There will be approximately 10-31 birth parents and their children participating at the San Diego site. There will be approximately 250-450 birth parent-child pairs participating at all 25 sites across the United States. </p>\n"
    }
   ],
   "visibleIf": "{fromInternal} = 'Yes'"
